heading: Community spirit takes centre stage at Hayleys Plantations Best Tea Harvester Competition
summary: The Best Tea Harvester Competition, hosted by Hayleys Plantations, celebrated the skills of tea harvesters in Sri Lanka. Overall Champion Anthony Iresha Rajaletchumi won Rs. 500,000 and a flat-screen TV for her performance. The event highlighted the importance of tea harvesters and included awards for top competitors across various estates.
content:
b'Spectators looking on as winners are recognised at Best Tea Harvester Competition awards ceremony
  Overall Champion Anthony Iresha Rajaletchumi of Great Western Estate (Talawakelle Tea Estates) receives Rs. 500,000 cash prize (totalling Rs. 650,000 with estate-level win) from Hayleys Group Chairman and Chief Executive, Mohan Pandithage, and Hayleys Plantations Managing Director Dr. Roshan Rajadurai, at Best Tea Harvester Competition awards ceremony
  A tea harvester in action during the competition
Expert judges from the Tea Research Institute evaluated competitors on yield and quality 
Rs. 500,000 cash prize and Singer flat-screen TV for Overall Winner
Event held amid strong community support and a festive atmosphere
In a resounding tribute to the skilful hands behind every cup of Pure Ceylon Tea, Hayleys Plantations hosted the third edition of its Best Tea Harvester Competition, an event hotly anticipated by plantation communities connected to Kelani Valley Plantations PLC (KVPL), Talawakelle Tea Estates PLC (TTE PLC) and Horana Plantations PLC (HPL). 

Hayleys Group Chairman and Chief Executive, Mohan Pandithage graced this special occasion along with Hayleys PLC Executive Director Sarath Ganegoda, Hayleys Plantations Managing Director Dr. Roshan Rajadurai and several other dignitaries. 

The competition transformed the Somerset Estate and Dimbula Cricket Club Grounds, into a vibrant hub of festivity, where families, co-workers and local community supporters gathered to cheer on the women whose expertise drives Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s tea industry. Over 40 women pluckers who won the estates\xe2\x80\x99 level competitions earned the opportunity to compete in the grand finale which consisted of 15 minutes of harvesting and 5 minutes of sorting. 

More than a contest of speed and volume, the event showcased the precision and care essential to producing tea of unparalleled quality. Expert judges from the Tea Research Institute evaluated the harvesters on yield, finesse, and quality of harvest. Red Cross and health officials were also onsite during the entire contest in order to ensure the safety of all participants and spectators. 

\xe2\x80\x9cThrough the hands of our cherished tea harvesters, Pure Ceylon Tea continues to be loved around the world. The Best Tea Harvester Competition is a celebration of their hard work, showing the commitment that keeps Ceylon Tea a global symbol of quality. This industry is a key part of our country\xe2\x80\x99s economy, helping thousands of families and strengthening Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s position on the world stage. 

\xe2\x80\x9cTo all the participants, finalists, and winners \xe2\x80\x93 you are the pride of this industry. Your efforts are integral to our shared success, and we committed to supporting, uplifting, and investing in each of you so that everyone has the opportunity to learn, and grow through safe, secure, dignified work,\xe2\x80\x9d said Hayleys Chairman and Chief Executive, Mohan Pandithage. 

Overall Champion, Anthony Iresha Rajaletchumi of Great Western Estate (TTE PLC) said, \xe2\x80\x9cI am so happy and truly grateful for this recognition. I want to thank my family, friends, and everyone at the estate including our manager who supported and encouraged and helped me prepare for today\xe2\x80\x99s competition.\xe2\x80\x9d 

Rajaletchumi harvested 6.2 kg in just 15 minutes, earning her a cash prize of Rs. 500,000 (in addition to a Rs. 150,000 estate-level cash prize for securing the Gold Award under TTE PLC). She was also awarded a flat-screen TV, sponsored by Singer Sri Lanka. The Silver Award went to Dharmalingam Poomany (Mattakelle Estate), while Veeriah Vanitha (Logie Estate) took Bronze. 

N. Indrakanthy (Ingestre Estate) claimed the Gold Award for KVPL, followed by Subramaniam Komathy (Battalgalla Estate) \xe2\x80\x93 Silver, and M. Mariyal (Fordyce Estate) \xe2\x80\x93 Bronze. Meanwhile, HPL recognised Sugumaran Rajaletchumy (Bambarakelly Estate) with Gold, K. Kavitha (Alton Estate) with Silver, and P. Chandraleka (Fairlawn Estate) with Bronze. 

All Gold, Silver, and Bronze winners across the three companies received cash prizes and portable speakers sponsored by Singer Sri Lanka. 

According to Hayleys Plantations Managing Director Dr. Roshan Rajadurai, the contest reaffirms Hayleys Plantations\xe2\x80\x99 commitment to recognising, uplifting, and honouring its workforce as a central pillar in its wider effort to lead the transformation of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s tea industry. 

\xe2\x80\x9cThis event is a testament to the spirit of camaraderie, partnership and appreciation that defines Hayleys Plantations. By listening to our workforce and celebrating their dedication, we\xe2\x80\x99re reinforcing the values of community, empowerment, and continuous improvement. As employers, it\xe2\x80\x99s our duty to establish systems in which merit and performance is fairly and reliably rewarded. These efforts are essential to our vision of leading Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s tea industry into globally celebrated leaders in ethical, sustainable, and high-quality production,\xe2\x80\x9d Dr. Rajadurai said. 

Hayleys Plantations, comprising of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s most certified and awarded plantations companies, continues to demonstrate leadership in its investments towards comprehensive workforce development, training programs, healthcare initiatives, and community engagement projects.  '
reasoning: The event celebrates and uplifts tea harvesters, enhancing community spirit and recognition in the tea industry, which is vital for Sri Lanka's economy. It promotes quality production and supports the workforce, leading to potential growth in agricultural businesses.

heading: AgriTech Conference 2025 brings innovation and entrepreneurship in agriculture to Jaffna
summary: The AgriTech Conference 2025, held at the University of Jaffna, brought together academics, industry leaders, and students to discuss technology and entrepreneurship in agriculture. The event featured keynote addresses, a problem-pitching session, and an exhibition showcasing innovations. It emphasized the importance of agripreneurship and collaboration for a sustainable agricultural future.
content:
b'The AgriTech Conference 2025, organised by the Faculty of Agriculture at the University of Jaffna in collaboration with the Sri Lanka Agripreneurs Forum (SLAF) and the Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA), successfully concluded at the university\xe2\x80\x99s Kilinochchi premises. 

This landmark event brought together a diverse group of stakeholders, including academics, industry leaders, agripreneurs, and students, to explore the intersection of technology and entrepreneurship in agriculture.

The conference featured a series of keynote addresses by renowned local and international experts, who shared their insights on sustainable farming, smart agriculture, and the latest innovations transforming the agricultural sector. These sessions provided a comprehensive overview of the challenges and opportunities facing modern agriculture, setting the stage for meaningful discussions and collaborations.

One of the most engaging aspects of the event was the problem-pitching session, where participants presented key agricultural challenges to experts. This was followed by interactive discussions and presentations by final-year research students, showcasing their innovative solutions for improving efficiency and sustainability. These sessions highlighted the creativity and dedication of future agricultural leaders.

Another major highlight was the AgriTech exhibition, where SLAF members and technology providers showcased cutting-edge products. Attendees explored innovations ranging from precision farming tools to sustainable practices, gaining valuable insights into the future of agriculture.

The SLAF conducted an inspiring session on agripreneurship, emphasising the critical role of entrepreneurship in driving agricultural innovation. The session introduced participants to the SLAF, outlining its mission, ongoing initiatives, and the support it provides to budding agripreneurs. By fostering collaboration between stakeholders, the SLAF is working to create a thriving ecosystem where innovative agricultural enterprises can flourish.

The AgriTech Conference 2025 was a great success, fostering connections and knowledge-sharing among stakeholders. By uniting academia, industry, and international partners, it has set the stage for a more innovative and sustainable future in agriculture. '
reasoning: The AgriTech Conference 2025 promotes innovation and entrepreneurship, which can significantly enhance agricultural practices and business opportunities in Sri Lanka. The collaboration among various stakeholders is likely to lead to sustainable growth in the sector.

heading: Korean Textile Trading Association and Brushes and Needles forge strategic partnership
summary: The Korean Textile Trading Association (KTTA) and Brushes and Needles Ltd. (B&N) signed a Memorandum of Understanding in Seoul to enhance sustainable Korean textiles in South Asia. This collaboration will be highlighted by the opening of the K-Textile Showroom in Colombo, promoting innovation and market expansion in the textile sector.
content:
b'  Representatives of B&N and KTTA signed the MoU in Seoul, Korea 
 Initiative aimed at elevating sustainable Korean textiles in South Asia, innovation, collaboration, and market expansion 
Collaboration will be marked by grand opening of K-Textile Showroom in Colombo, today at Verticle by Jetwing
In a strategic initiative to advance international trade, emphasising sustainability and innovation, the Korean Textile Trading Association (KTTA) and Brushes and Needles Ltd. (B&N) have announced their strategic collaboration, paving the way for greater cooperation between Sri Lanka and South Korea in the textile and apparel sector. The collaboration will be marked by the grand opening of the K-Textile Showroom in Colombo, today (20 March) at Verticle by Jetwing, Access Towers. This initiative represents a major step in bridging advanced South Korean textile technology with Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s globally renewed apparel industry, fostering knowledge sharing, business expansion, and market innovation. With South Korea being a global leader in high-quality textiles and Sri Lanka renowned for its strong apparel manufacturing sector, this collaboration is expected to drive significant synergies. The showroom will serve as a hub for premium textile solutions, offering Sri Lankan manufacturers access to innovative and sustainable fabrics while providing South Korean suppliers a gateway to the South Asian market. This partnership signifies a long-term commitment to enhancing trade, innovation, and sustainability in the textile industry. By leveraging South Korea\xe2\x80\x99s cutting-edge textile technology, Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s apparel industry\xe2\x80\x99s expects to elevate its high FOB product offer to global fashion industry. 

The Korean Textile Trading Association (KTTA) is a leading organisation representing South Korea\xe2\x80\x99s textile exporters and manufacturers. KTTA has been instrumental in promoting global trade and ensuring that Korean textiles remain at the forefront of the global fashion and apparel industry.

Brushes and Needles, a Sri Lankan-based one-stop solution provider for global fashion brands, specialising in premium textile sourcing, supply chain management, and innovation-driven solutions. With a strong commitment to sustainability and ethical manufacturing, B&N has played a crucial role in advancing Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s textile industry.

Industry leaders and policymakers anticipate that this collaboration will create new business opportunities, enhance supply chain efficiencies, and contribute to Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s positioning as a regional leader in apparel manufacturing.

The grand opening will be attended by government officials, industry stakeholders, and media representatives, underscoring the importance of international partnerships in driving sustainable innovation and economic growth.
 '
reasoning: The collaboration between KTTA and B&N is expected to enhance Sri Lanka's apparel industry by providing access to innovative textiles and fostering international trade, which will create new business opportunities and elevate the country's market position.

heading: Kudos to Brandix as Sri Lankas Best Logistics Performer to US, Canada by PVH
summary: Brandix Apparel has been named the Overall Best Performer for the third consecutive year by PVH for its exports to the USA and Canada. Recognized for excellence in document, delivery, and booking timelines, Brandix's commitment to customer requirements and sustainability highlights its leadership in apparel manufacturing and digital solutions.
content:
b'Brandix Apparel has been recognised as the Overall Best Performer for the third consecutive year by global fashion giant PVH for its exports to the USA and Canada from Sri Lanka.

At PVH\xe2\x80\x99s annual vendor performance workshop, held recently in Colombo, Brandix topped all key performance indexes, scoring the highest among PVH vendors in Sri Lanka for discipline in document timelines, delivery timelines, and booking timelines, in addition to being the Overall Best Performer. The event took place at Maersk Lanka, PVH\xe2\x80\x99s logistics partner of choice.This recognition from PVH, the parent company of brands such as Tommy Hilfiger and Calvin Klein, in collaboration with Maersk, underscores Brandix\xe2\x80\x99s commitment to excellence in meeting customer requirements.

Brandix Group Supply Chain Director Afham Ali said: \xe2\x80\x9cThe supply chain in our industry is fast-paced, action-packed, and dynamic. To navigate this turbulent terrain, we remain closely attuned to our customers\xe2\x80\x99 requirements and meet them promptly with agile, innovative, and sustainable solutions. This recognition from a highly strategic customer strengthens and encourages us to aim even higher.\xe2\x80\x9d

With over 50 years of experience, Brandix is a global leader in apparel manufacturing and digital solutions, serving iconic brands worldwide.

 Its vertically integrated supply chain spans Sri Lanka, India, Bangladesh, Haiti, the UK, and the US. Driven by curiosity and a commitment to environmental and social sustainability, Brandix has achieved world firsts in ethical manufacturing. The company builds life-long relationships with partners who share its purpose, manufacturing Inspired Solutions for clothing that drive prosperity for all.

 '
reasoning: The recognition of Brandix as the Best Logistics Performer enhances the reputation of Sri Lankan apparel businesses, potentially attracting more international clients and boosting exports. This positive acknowledgment reflects the industry's capability and commitment to excellence, which can lead to increased business opportunities.

heading: Excel World launches first-ever Ramadan Kareem Iftar buffet
summary: Excel World Entertainment Park in Colombo has launched its first Ramadan Kareem Iftar buffet, available daily until 30 March from 6 p.m. to 10 p.m. The buffet features traditional dishes, entertainment, and a family-friendly atmosphere, including a prayer space. The event has received positive feedback and aims to become a lasting tradition.
content:
b'Excel World Entertainment Park in Colombo recently celebrated the launch of its first-ever Ramadan Kareem Iftar buffet, offering a distinctive and memorable way to experience the holy month. The Iftar buffet, available daily until 30 March from 6 p.m. to 10 p.m. is designed to offer both culinary delights and entertainment in a unique, welcoming atmosphere.
At the inaugural event, the evening began with the Maghrib prayer, followed by the opening of the Iftar buffet. Guests were able to indulge in a specially curated selection of traditional Ramadan dishes, including dates, fresh juice and savoury appetisers such as crispy chicken samosas, spicy Maldivian fish patties and succulent fish rolls. The buffet also featured main dishes such as the flavoursome chicken kanji and mouth-watering chicken shawarma, alongside indulgent desserts such as gulab jamun and carrot halva. After the meal, the Isha prayer was observed, allowing guests to pause for spiritual reflection before continuing their evening.

The exclusivity of Excel World\xe2\x80\x99s Iftar buffet lies in its combination of delicious food paired with family-friendly offerings. While breaking fast, guests could also enjoy the excitement of the venue\xe2\x80\x99s theme park activities, catering to all ages. The space\xe2\x80\x99s vibrant atmosphere ensures a balanced experience of fun and spiritual reflection, with a dedicated prayer space made available for guests to observe their religious practices in comfort and peace.

The Iftar buffet is affordably priced, making it an excellent choice for families and groups looking to enjoy a unique Ramadan experience. Whether one is seeking a place to reflect, indulge in traditional dishes or enjoy some family time, Excel World provides a special setting for every guest.

The inaugural Iftar buffet has already garnered tremendous enthusiasm from the local community, and its success has set the stage for it to become a long-anticipated tradition in the coming years. The buffet is available daily until 30 March at Excel World, Colombo. 
 '
reasoning: The launch of the Iftar buffet at Excel World provides a unique dining experience that caters to families and the local community, enhancing the food and beverage sector during Ramadan. This initiative is likely to boost business and attract more customers, contributing positively to the industry.

heading: Chill Colombo: New culinary and nightlife destination at Port City Colombo
summary: Chill Colombo has opened in Port City Colombo, offering an upscale dining experience with a menu that blends local and international flavors. Designed by architect Maria, the restaurant features chic interiors and outdoor seating. It serves a variety of dishes and cocktails, transforming from a dining venue to a nightlife hub.
content:
b'A new era of upscale dining has arrived in the heart of Port City Colombo with the grand opening of Chill Colombo. Located at The Mall at Port City Colombo, this two-storey restaurant, bar, and caf\xc3\xa9 brings an elevated culinary and nightlife experience, blending local and international flavours in an atmosphere of contemporary elegance.

With a carefully curated menu and a sophisticated yet inviting ambience, Chill Colombo caters to various dining preferences, from casual brunches and wholesome family meals to refined dining experiences and lively nightlife. The restaurant\xe2\x80\x99s chic interiors, designed by renowned Spanish architect Maria, complement its bohemian-inspired outdoor seating, creating a seamless fusion of modern luxury and artistic charm.


As the sister restaurant of the globally celebrated Chill Ella, which was ranked #2 in TripAdvisor\xe2\x80\x99s Travellers\xe2\x80\x99 Choice Awards for \xe2\x80\x9cBest Casual Dining\xe2\x80\x9d in 2024, Chill Colombo carries a legacy of excellence. Founded by Darshana Ratnayake, the brand has become synonymous with Sri Lankan hospitality, culinary artistry, and vibrant social experiences. \xe2\x80\x9cBringing Chill to Colombo has been a long-awaited dream,\xe2\x80\x9d said Darshana. \xe2\x80\x9cFor years, we received countless requests to establish a presence in the city. When the opportunity arose to open at The Mall at Port City Colombo, we knew it was the perfect location. Chill Colombo is not just about food; it\xe2\x80\x99s about the experience \xe2\x80\x93 an immersive journey through flavours, textures, and design that reflects our commitment to culinary innovation and hospitality.\xe2\x80\x9d

Chill Colombo offers an extensive menu that seamlessly blends Sri Lankan authenticity with international influences. Signature dishes include the Negombo Tiger Prawns, traditional Lamprais, Nasi Goreng, artisan pizzas, handmade pasta, and risottos, alongside a variety of Asian and Western delicacies inspired by Indian, Mexican, French, Italian and Chinese cuisine.

Every dish is crafted precisely, using high-quality local and international ingredients to deliver bold, vibrant flavours. Menus are designed to cater to diverse palates, whether guests seek wholesome vegetarian options, indulgent comfort food, or refined gourmet creations.

The bar and beverage menu is equally impressive, featuring a creative selection of expertly crafted cocktails and mocktails. The in-house mixologists incorporate Sri Lankan spices, tropical infusions, and premium spirits, ensuring a unique and refreshing drinking experience. Whether guests prefer a bold, smoky classic or a light, fruit-forward concoction, the bar at Chill Colombo promises a masterful selection of drinks.


By day, Chill Colombo offers a refined dining experience, providing a tranquil escape for guests to enjoy a leisurely meal or coffee break. As the evening unfolds, the venue transforms into a vibrant social hub, with live music, DJs, and performances elevating the atmosphere. Unlike many dining establishments in Colombo, Chill Colombo extends its hours until 2 a.m. on weekends, positioning itself as a go-to destination for late-night entertainment and social gatherings.

\xe2\x80\x9cWe envisioned Chill Colombo as more than just a restaurant\xe2\x80\x94it\xe2\x80\x99s a space that evolves with the day,\xe2\x80\x9d said Darshana. \xe2\x80\x9cWhether you\xe2\x80\x99re enjoying a relaxed brunch, an intimate dinner, or a lively night out with friends, we\xe2\x80\x99ve created an experience that adapts to your mood.\xe2\x80\x9d


With seating for over 150 guests across its ground floor, first floor, terrace, and outdoor dining areas, the restaurant offers a comfortable yet elevated semi-fine dining experience. The interiors exude a cosmopolitan charm, blending local craftsmanship with modern aesthetics. Natural wood accents, custom-designed lighting, and elegantly curved architectural elements create a sophisticated and inviting ambience.

Chill Colombo\xe2\x80\x99s origins trace back to Caf\xc3\xa9 Chill Ella, which began as a humble caf\xc3\xa9 in 2009 and has since grown into one of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s most celebrated dining establishments. Over the years, the brand has expanded significantly, gaining international recognition for its commitment to exceptional service, high-quality cuisine, and immersive dining experiences.


\xe2\x80\x9cOur philosophy has always been about creating memorable moments,\xe2\x80\x9d Darshana explained. \xe2\x80\x9cFrom the moment guests step inside, we want them to feel at home \xe2\x80\x93 to indulge in the aromas of our kitchen, the warmth of our hospitality, and the energy of the space. Chill Colombo continues that legacy, now brought to the city.\xe2\x80\x9d

As the latest addition to Colombo\xe2\x80\x99s vibrant dining scene, Chill Colombo sets a new standard for upscale dining and entertainment. With its stunning interiors, dynamic menu, and commitment to world-class service, the restaurant promises to be a sought-after destination for locals and international visitors. For reservations and inquiries, contact 011 233 5428.'
reasoning: The opening of Chill Colombo enhances the culinary landscape in Sri Lanka, attracting both locals and tourists, which can significantly boost the Food & Beverage sector. Its upscale dining and nightlife offerings are likely to increase overall consumer spending in the area.

heading: Dialog Enterprise and Huawei drive digital innovation with Wi-Fi 7 for future-ready businesses
summary: Dialog Enterprise, the ICT solutions arm of Dialog Axiata, has launched Sri Lanka's first Wi-Fi 7 network in partnership with Huawei at SLIIT and The Kingsbury Hotel. This advanced network enhances connectivity for various sectors, offering speeds up to four times faster than previous technologies, and supports industries like education, hospitality, healthcare, and manufacturing.
content:
b'Dialog Enterprise, the corporate ICT solutions arm of Dialog Axiata, continues to lead the way in delivering enterprise-grade wireless connectivity, empowering businesses with high-performance networking solutions. As a pioneer in Business Connectivity, Dialog Enterprise has deployed advanced wireless connectivity solutions across corporate offices, industrial factory floors, and leading hospitality venues, ensuring seamless connectivity tailored to the unique demands of each sector.

Taking a significant step forward, Dialog Enterprise, in collaboration with the global technology innovator Huawei, has now deployed Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s first Wi-Fi 7 network at two key partner locations: the Sri Lanka Institute of Information Technology (SLIIT) and The Kingsbury Hotel. These deployments mark the beginning of a nationwide transformation, bringing next-generation wireless capabilities to organisations that demand high-speed, ultra-reliable, and secure connectivity.

Wi-Fi 7 is designed to cater to environments with high traffic, a vast number of connected devices, and extreme throughput requirements. Using the latest 6 GHz spectrum, 4K-QAM modulation, and Multi-Link Operation (MLO), Wi-Fi 7 delivers speeds up to four times faster than its predecessor, with significantly lower latency. This makes it ideal for industries requiring real-time collaboration, high-definition video streaming, large-scale cloud applications, and AI-driven operations.

At SLIIT, the Wi-Fi 7 deployment enhances virtual learning, collaborative research, and an enriched student experience, supporting the institution\xe2\x80\x99s digital-first approach to education. At The Kingsbury Hotel, ultra-fast, high-capacity Wi-Fi ensures guests enjoy buffer-free streaming, seamless remote work, and smart room integrations for an enhanced hospitality experience. Beyond education and hospitality, Wi-Fi 7 has the potential to impact industries such as healthcare, manufacturing, and security. It could enable real-time telemedicine, rapid transfer of large medical files, and IoT-enabled smart medical devices in healthcare. In manufacturing, the ultra-fast network may support smart factory automation, seamless
device communication, and predictive maintenance analytics. For security and defence, Wi-Fi 7\xe2\x80\x99s low latency and advanced encryption capabilities could enhance real-time surveillance and rapid data processing for critical infrastructure.

Huawei Sri Lanka Enterprise Business Vice President Hao Zhiqiang said: \xe2\x80\x9cWi-Fi 7 represents a major leap in connectivity, enabling industries to meet growing digital demands with greater speed, capacity, and security. Our partnership with Dialog Enterprise ensures businesses benefit from cutting-edge wireless solutions that drive innovation and efficiency.\xe2\x80\x9d 

Dialog Enterprise Group Chief Officer Navin Pieris said: \xe2\x80\x9cWi-Fi 7 represents a transformative leap in connectivity, enabling organisations to meet the ever-growing demands of digital transformation. Whether in education, hospitality, or enterprise, our goal is to provide cutting-edge wireless solutions that deliver exceptional performance, reliability, and security.

\xe2\x80\x9cOur collaboration with leading global partners ensures we bring best-in-class innovations to our customers, helping them stay ahead in a hyper-connected world,\xe2\x80\x9d he added.

By deploying Wi-Fi 7, Dialog Enterprise reaffirms its commitment to working closely with businesses, institutions, and industries to deliver tailored solutions that meet their evolving connectivity needs. As digital adoption accelerates, this initiative lays the foundation for next-generation networking across Sri Lanka, empowering businesses with superior speed, efficiency, and security.'
reasoning: The deployment of Wi-Fi 7 by Dialog Enterprise and Huawei significantly enhances connectivity for various sectors in Sri Lanka, driving digital transformation and innovation. This advancement is expected to empower businesses with superior networking capabilities, fostering growth and efficiency.

heading: ASUS unveils AI-powered laptops
summary: ASUS has launched its 2025 AI-powered laptop lineup, including the Vivobook 14 Flip, Zenbook DUO, and Zenbook 14, featuring Intel Core Ultra processors with integrated NPUs. These laptops cater to professionals and students, offering advanced multitasking capabilities, stunning OLED displays, and long battery life, available in Sri Lanka's ASUS stores.
content:
b'ASUS, a Taiwanese tech giant is set to push the boundaries of innovation with its latest lineup of AI-powered laptops offering versatile performance, stunning design, and multiple use case options for enhanced productivity and entertainment. 
The brand\xe2\x80\x99s first lineup of 2025 not only caters to a new segment but also makes AI more accessible than ever, the lineup features Vivobook 14 Flip, Zenbook DUO and Zenbook 14 powered by the Latest Intel Core Ultra Series of processors, featuring integrated NPU (Neural Processing Units) that deliver up to 47 TOPS (Teraflops of Operation Per Second). These new ASUS AI PCs lineups are aimed at working professionals, students, creators, multitaskers. The products will be accessible at the ASUS Exclusive Stores and selected multi-brand stores across Sri Lanka. 
The Vivobook 14 Flip measures up to just 1.1 cm thin and weighs only 1.2 kg. It is equipped with Up to the latest Intel Core Ultra 7 (Series 2) processor and a 47 TOPS NPU, delivering advanced AI capabilities. Efficient multitasking is supported by 16 GB of LPDDR5X RAM and 1TB M.2 NVMe PCIe 4.0 SSD. The 14 Flip supports different orientations and can be used in laptop, tent, clamshell or tablet modes. It also sports the ASUS Lumina OLED panel with 60Hz refresh rate for smooth viewing experiences and is backed with a high-capacity 70 WHr battery. 
The upgraded Zenbook DUO comes with a Dual OLED Touchscreen display, alongside a detachable full-size keyboard and built-in kickstand. It is powered by Intel Core Ultra 9 processor 285H with a 13 TOPS NPU, providing everyday AI capabilities. It comes with 32 GB of LPDDR5X RAM and a 1TB M.2 NVMe PCIe 4.0 SSD for high-speed performance and ample storage, all backed by a 75 WHr battery. 

The new ASUS Zenbook 14 features the latest by Intel Core Ultra 5 processor with a 13 TOPS NPU, delivering great everyday AI capabilities. It has a 16 GB LPDDR5X RAM and a blazing-fast 1 TB PCIe Gen 4.0 SSD. With a 16:10 aspect ratio ASUS Lumina OLED touchscreen display that delivers immersive viewing experiences. It packs with a 75 WHr battery as well and can deliver up to 18 hours of usage on a single charge.'
reasoning: The introduction of AI-powered laptops by ASUS enhances the tech landscape in Sri Lanka, providing advanced technology and boosting local businesses through increased accessibility and innovation. This can lead to growth in the IT sector and attract more consumers to tech products.

heading: Prime Group unveils PrimeMax to redefine homeownership and wealth creation
summary: Prime Group launched PrimeMax on 16 March in Colombo, a homeownership and investment plan aimed at making property ownership more accessible in Sri Lanka. With a 10% down payment and 0.5% monthly installments, it offers financial flexibility for aspiring homeowners and investors, promoting long-term wealth creation and simplified processes.
content:
b'  Never before 10% down payment and just 0.5% monthly 
Big Dreams. Small Payments
In a groundbreaking move set to transform Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s real estate landscape, Prime Group has introduced PrimeMax, an innovative homeownership and investment plan designed to simplify property ownership while fostering long-term wealth creation. The official unveiling of PrimeMax took place on 16 March at Shangri-La, Colombo, where industry leaders, financial experts, and prospective homeowners gathered to witness the launch of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s most revolutionary homeownership and investment solution.

For years, homebuyers have faced affordability challenges, while investors have sought more strategic ways to capitalise on real estate appreciation. With an unprecedented 10% down payment and a monthly instalment of just 0.5%, PrimeMax removes barriers to entry, providing financial flexibility while the asset appreciates, essentially reshaping the market by introducing a structure that ensures low upfront commitment and long-term financial gains.

This makes PrimeMax Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s most accessible and strategic real estate solution, catering to aspiring homeowners seeking an affordable path to securing their first home or expanding their real estate portfolio and seasoned investors looking for long-term value appreciation and seamless entry into high-value real estate markets, with a flexibility to invest in multiple properties. 

\xe2\x80\x9cAt Prime Group, we have always believed in innovation beyond spaces. With PrimeMax, we are not just building homes \xe2\x80\x94 we are delivering dreams and creating a smarter way for Sri Lankans to own property and maximise their financial future,\xe2\x80\x9d said Prime Group Group Co-Chairman Premalal Brahmanage. 

Real estate has consistently proven to be one of the most stable and rewarding investment avenues, with property values steadily appreciating in Sri Lanka. PrimeMax offers a strategic way to build equity with minimal initial investment and sustainable monthly commitments, all without bulk payments or complex paperwork, ensuring a seamless ownership experience for both homeowners and investors.

\xe2\x80\x9cWe understand that homeownership and real estate investment go hand in hand. PrimeMax ensures that both buyers and investors gain financial security, appreciation benefits, and a simplified process to grow their wealth effortlessly,\xe2\x80\x9d added Prime Group Co-Chairperson Sandamini Perera. 

Prime Group invites Sri Lankans to step into a new era \xe2\x80\x93 one where financial limitations no longer hold back their dreams. With PrimeMax, you can now max your dreams, max your wealth, and max your future.

For more information, visit www.primelands.lk or www.primeresidencies.lk contact 0710 773 773 or 0710 933 333. '
reasoning: The introduction of PrimeMax significantly lowers the barriers to homeownership, making it more accessible for a larger segment of the population, which is likely to stimulate demand in the property market. This innovative financing model can lead to increased investment in real estate, benefiting construction businesses and the overall economy.

heading: Property market shows signs of growth despite high taxes, bureaucratic hurdles
summary: Industry experts at the Lanka Property Show 2025 expressed optimism for Sri Lanka's real estate sector, citing potential growth despite previous economic challenges. The event showcased over 25 projects and attracted over 17,000 visitors. Discussions highlighted the need for policy stability, affordable housing, and streamlined investment processes to ensure sustainable growth in the market.
content:
b'  Industry experts at the Lanka Property Show 2025 expressed confidence in Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s real estate sector, highlighting its potential for growth despite past economic challenges. While factors such as rising interest rates, currency depreciation, and fluctuating taxes previously impacted the market, experts were optimistic that stabilising interest rates, exchange rates, and tax policies will foster a more predictable and business-friendly environment for investors and homebuyers alike.

Building on this positive outlook, the Lanka Property Show 2025 reinforced the sector\xe2\x80\x99s resilience and promising future. The event featured over 25 premier projects, including highly anticipated new launches, attracting a diverse audience of over 17,000 visitors both in person and virtually. The live stream on Facebook, LinkedIn, and YouTube also garnered an impressive 59,721 views, further cementing the show\xe2\x80\x99s success. The strong turnout and enthusiastic engagement from buyers, investors, and industry professionals underscored the sustained demand for real estate in Sri Lanka.

Now in its ninth edition, the Lanka Property Show (LPS) \xe2\x80\x94 the country\xe2\x80\x99s largest property expo  \xe2\x80\x94 was held on 15 and 16 February at the Kingsbury Hotel. Since its inception in 2017, the event has grown significantly, and in recent years, it has evolved into a hybrid physical and virtual show. This year saw an increase in visitors and exhibitors, reaffirming that buyers are actively returning to the market after the pandemic and economic downturn.

As in past editions, the Lanka Property Show 2025 hosted two engaging panel discussions, offering valuable industry insights. The first session delved into the growth and future of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s property sector, examining key trends and market projections.

Kicking off the discussion, former Governor of the Central Bank Dr. Indrajit Coomaraswamy, shared his perspective on the evolving economic landscape. He noted that, unlike in the past, challenges such as high interest rates, currency depreciation, and tax instability are expected to stabilise. This shift, driven by stricter fiscal policies introduced through the Public Finance Management Act and the Central Bank Act, is set to create a more predictable and investment-friendly environment.

Discussing the current market landscape for developers, Prime Group Chairman, Premalal Brahmanage, highlighted that Sri Lanka has the highest construction costs in South Asia, making property development more expensive and limiting the supply of affordable housing. He emphasised the financial burden on developers, stating that from the first bag of cement to the final sale, direct and indirect taxes can account for up to 40% of each property transaction.

With the real estate industry contributing around 7% to the country\xe2\x80\x99s GDP and generating substantial tax revenue, he urged the Government to provide greater support to the sector to ensure its sustained growth and affordability for buyers.

To address these challenges, the industry is actively exploring innovative solutions such as cheaper financing options, enhanced supply chains, and advanced construction techniques to improve affordability and sustainability in the market, added Brahmanage.

In summary of Brahmanage\xe2\x80\x99s comments, the moderator, Dhananath Fernando, remarked, \xe2\x80\x9cit sounds to me like you\xe2\x80\x99re in the business of paying taxes and in the middle of it building some property\xe2\x80\x9d.

Addressing the challenges developers face in attracting foreign buyers, Platinum Realty Investments Managing Director Kishore Reddy, urged the Government to expedite the implementation of investor visas. Despite being gazetted, these visas remain difficult to obtain, posing a barrier to international investment in Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s property market. He highlighted the need to make housing more affordable by addressing import barriers on essential building materials such as tiles, aluminium, and other construction materials. The imposition of cess and high duties on these imports increases construction costs, ultimately impacting both developers and buyers. By reducing such restrictions, the Government can facilitate more cost-effective development. He also noted that while the Rupee has depreciated against the dollar, property values have risen proportionally, ensuring that investors have not faced losses. This natural market adjustment, he emphasised, reinforces the view that real estate remains a secure and reliable investment option.

The panel discussion, moderated by Advocata Institute CEO Dhananath Fernando, also featured John Keells Holdings PLC Vice President Nadeem Shums and Sri Lanka Atomic Energy Regulatory Council Chairman and Property Law Consultant Saminda Jayasekara, providing an in-depth and balanced view of the future trajectory of the market.

Continuing with the theme of real estate and construction, the second panel discussion centred on the affordable construction of individual homes.

Moderated by University of Sri Jayewardenepura Head of the Department of Estate Management and Valuation Dr. Prathap Kaluthanthri, the panel featured Head of the University of Sri Jayewardenepura Department of Business Economics Dr. Janaka Fernando, Business Consultant Dr. Yasas Pathiranage, Urban Development Authority Deputy Director General Plnr. E.A.C. Piyashantha, and Chartered Architect Partner, Makevita and Ranathungarachchi Architects, Tharangika Ranathungarachchi.

The discussion covered vital themes for those looking to build houses, including passive design, locally sourced materials, adaptive design, green roofs and living walls, all aimed at reducing costs, improving efficiency, and enhancing affordability and sustainability of houses.

Concluding the discussions, industry experts emphasised the need for policy stability, affordable housing solutions, and streamlined investment processes to drive growth. With strong buyer interest, increased investor confidence, and ongoing discussions on key industry challenges, the event highlighted a promising path forward for the sector. As Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s property market continues to evolve, collaborative efforts between stakeholders and policymakers will be crucial in ensuring sustainable growth and greater accessibility for both local and foreign buyers.

This year\xe2\x80\x99s event truly embodied its theme, \xe2\x80\x9cEverything Under One Roof for Property Buyers,\xe2\x80\x9d by bringing together a comprehensive range of real estate opportunities and services. Exhibitors showcased a diverse selection of apartments, houses, and land projects across the country, while four leading banks offered home loans starting from 11.5%. Attendees also had access to house builders, solar providers, free legal consultations, and expert advisory services on buying and selling \xe2\x80\x94 all conveniently available under one roof throughout the two-day event to fulfil their property buying process in the same location.

It was made possible with the support of its esteemed sponsors and partners. Platinum sponsors included Marina Square, John Keells Properties and Iconic Galaxy, while Gold sponsors included Baili Investment and Prime Group. The event was further supported by its Banking Partner, Commercial Bank along with the media partnership of Sirasa Media Network, Outdoor Media Partner Storm Media and Communication Partner Textware.
 '
reasoning: The article highlights a growing confidence in Sri Lanka's real estate sector, with increased investor interest and a more predictable environment for property development. The successful Lanka Property Show 2025 indicates strong demand and potential for growth in the market.

heading: Taj Samudra, Colombo celebrates Earth Hour 2025
summary: Taj Samudra, Colombo celebrated Earth Hour by dimming non-essential lights at 8:30 p.m., creating a candlelit ambiance for guests and associates. The event focused on energy conservation and sustainability, featuring meaningful conversations and eco-friendly activities. The hotel reaffirmed its commitment to combining luxury with environmental responsibility.
content:
b'Taj Samudra, Colombo joined the global Earth Hour movement by hosting a special celebration with in-house guests, Area Director Maldives and Sri Lanka and General Manager Samrat Datta, and the hotel\xe2\x80\x99s associates. The event aimed to raise awareness about energy conservation and sustainability.
As the clock struck 8:30 p.m. the hotel dimmed its non-essential lights, creating a serene ambiance illuminated by candlelight. Guests participated in an evening of meaningful conversations and eco-friendly activities, reinforcing the commitment to a greener future.
The associates and guests wholeheartedly supported the cause, making Earth Hour 2025 a memorable and impactful event.
Taj Samudra, Colombo said it continues to champion sustainability, ensuring that luxury and environmental responsibility go hand in hand.'
reasoning: The event promotes sustainability and energy conservation, which can enhance the hotel's reputation and attract eco-conscious travelers. This positive engagement can lead to increased patronage and support for the local tourism sector.

heading: Sri Lanka participates in international tourism promotion event Ferien Messe Wien  2025 in Vienna
summary: The Sri Lanka Tourism Promotion Bureau, alongside the Sri Lankan Embassy in Vienna, successfully participated in the Ferien Messe Wien  2025 from January 16-19, 2025. The event attracted over 71,000 visitors and showcased Sri Lanka's culture, cuisine, and tourism potential, enhancing its visibility among European travelers, particularly Austrians.
content:
b'Sri Lanka Tourism Promotion Bureau, in collaboration with the Embassy of Sri Lanka in Vienna, participated in the \xe2\x80\x9cFerien Messe Wien \xe2\x80\x93 2025\xe2\x80\x9d, the 46th International Tourism Promotion event in Vienna from 16 to 19 January 2025. Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s participation was a resounding success with every effort taken to promote \xe2\x80\x9cSri Lanka brand\xe2\x80\x9d among European travellers, especially among Austrians.

Ferien Messe Wien \xe2\x80\x93 2025 attracted more than 71,000 visitors, offering them a blend of breathtaking experiences, global travel trends and exciting entertainment. With the participation of over 430 national and international exhibitors, the event provided an unparalleled platform to showcase destinations, culinary delights and cultural traditions.

The Sri Lanka stand at the event added a vibrant and exotic holiday atmosphere to visitors\xe2\x80\x99 experience, highlighting Sri Lanka as one of the world\xe2\x80\x99s most captivating destinations. It reflected the country\xe2\x80\x99s massive touristic potential, and displayed exquisite traditional handicrafts, such as wooden masks and branded elephants, tea boutique counter and promotional items including Sri Lankan branded caps, key tags and brochures. Ceylon tea was served to the guests who visited the stand.


The Sri Lanka stand was inaugurated by Ambassador of Sri Lanka to Austria M.R.K. Lenagala. In his remarks, the Ambassador appreciated the commitment of the participating travel/tour operators and tour companies. The Ambassador also commended their valuable contributions to attract tourists to Sri Lanka which is evident from the increasing numbers. Representatives from the Delux Holidays Ltd., B H Lanka Ltd., Aitken Spence Travels, Serene Vacations Lanka Ltd., Butterflies Ltd., Travel Trends Leisure Ltd., Camlo Lanka Tours, Celestia Ayurveda Resort, Walkers Tours Ltd., Jagath Tours and Travels, Wanderlustasia, Lotus Destinations Lanka Ltd., Ocean Gate Travels and Tours Ltd., were present at the Sri Lanka stand.

Sri Lanka was allocated one slot at the main stage per day, scheduled during peak hours to maximise engagement with the audience. A German language video presentation and Sri Lanka upcountry and low country dance performances were featured at the main stage. SLTB Junior Manager \xe2\x80\x93 Strategic Planning and Research Jagath Perera delivered the welcome speech on each day featuring the traditional Sri Lankan greeting \xe2\x80\x9cAyubowan\xe2\x80\x9d and emphasis on Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s unique attractions.

The Popular Tik Tok bloggers of Goofy.tv, Colja and Gabriel shared experiences gained during their 14-day media familiarisation tour in Sri Lanka with the audience. The content they published on TikTok on the tour to Sri Lanka has garnered two million views, significantly boosting Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s visibility among younger audiences. In addition, the renowned author of \xe2\x80\x9cSri Lanka \xe2\x80\x93 faszinierende Begegnungen (Fascinating Encounters)\xe2\x80\x9d, Renate Reisch shared her insights and experiences. This was followed by a presentation by the winner of the last year\xe2\x80\x99s raffle draw, David Rodriguez Coronado regarding his 14-day tour experience in Sri Lanka, which captivated the audience with his vivid storytelling.

The \xe2\x80\x9cExperience of the Exotic Flavours of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x9d presented by Sri Lankan Chef Ruwan Fernando, who has over 25 years of experience in the culinary sector was one of the most vibrant and attractive events for the visitors. Chef Fernando prepared iconic Sri Lankan dishes including kottu roti, vegetable roti, and \xe2\x80\x9cspecial spicy curries\xe2\x80\x9d using authentic Sri Lankan spices while holding culinary sessions. It attracted crowds who were delighted to taste Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s rich and diverse flavours.

The award-winning wildlife film \xe2\x80\x9cThe Great Elephant Gathering of Asia (Minneriya National Park)\xe2\x80\x9d was screened on the second day of the event. The screening was supported by Oshini Alagiyawanna.

In parallel to the main event, the Embassy of Sri Lanka in Vienna organised three cultural food promotional events at three popular shopping malls in Vienna. The massive audiences were served with Sri Lankan cuisine and Ceylon tea, showcasing the Sri Lankan hospitality. Moreover, Pradeep Wickramesinghe\xe2\x80\x99s dancing group in Milan performed traditional dances.

Quiz and raffle draw programs were conducted by the SLTPB in collaboration with three tour operating companies, at the three shopping malls. Winners received travel vouchers to stay 5 days in Sri Lanka with wellness packages and Ayurveda treatments. Prizes were distributed through the Embassy of Sri Lanka in Vienna, generating excitement and goodwill among attendees.

Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s participation in the \xe2\x80\x9cFerien Messe Wien \xe2\x80\x93 2025\xe2\x80\x9d received extensive media attention across television, social media platforms and news outlets. The showcasing of Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s unique culture, heritage and tourism attractions to an international audience for four days enhanced the country brand recognition among many stakeholders. The program boosted Sri Lanka\xe2\x80\x99s image as a must-visit destination among European and Austrian travellers, strengthening the country\xe2\x80\x99s position as a preferred long-haul destination.  
 '
reasoning: Sri Lanka's participation in the international tourism event significantly enhanced its visibility and brand recognition among European travelers, particularly Austrians, which is likely to lead to increased tourist arrivals. The successful promotion of Sri Lanka's unique culture and attractions at a major event indicates a strong potential for growth in tourism revenue.
